Upscaler has the correct default values however this should still be able to be changed by the user, I've also put some cliptext encodes so the user can also prompt different (just like the rest) 

The user should also be able to change the upscale model

The image node isn't connected because the user should have the ability to connect the image from IPAdapter #1 - if they do not want that then they can use this inpout

This habit should be carried on throughout the IPAdapter functions

CivitAI Checkpoint Loader gives us the ability to get any Civitai Checkpoint on the website (https://civitai.com)

THey will need to add their ckpt_air which follows this format {model_id}@{model_version} - it isn't mandatory assumng they add the model name from the list below the ckpt_air - if it set to none then the ckpt_air code is needed or they must put in a checkpoint in

it would be advised to add a tip to the user to know how to get an AIR code

This is not the same as CTE, it is a random prompt function in which the user can generate multiple times and have different results without the user necessarily having to change the seed

{} - indicates a collection and this collection will be randomized

within the collection it will have "|" and this means it will choose whatever is within that collection

for exmaple {jacket|blouse|t-shirt}. when this is ran, it will pick one out of those 3 

another example, in the random prompt below it has
"{black|blue|orange|white|green|purple} {jacket|blouse|t-shirt|dress|gym bra}"

this means that the function will choose either
Black Jacket
Blue Jacket
Ornage Jacket 
White Jacket
Green Jacket
Purple Jacket

Black Blouse
Blue Blouse
--- and so on

the user should be able to edit the seed and control after generate

Efficient Loaders must ALL have options available for the user to edit - all controlnet CNET stackers lead to the efficient loader cnet stacker

if a user wants to use multiple controlnets they must connect cnet_stack to CNET_STACK

IPA is similar to controlnet and is connected to model, it can be stacked up 

the load IPA model is area specific meaning if you choose the "ip-adapter-plus-face" it will try to implement that face into AI image that is being generated (it is NOT a replacement for deepfake, it is not better than deepfake)

Noise will determine how much the image will listen to the prompt, it is by default at 1, if at 0 it will try to match the base image loaded into the IPA

Linear, original and channel penalty are also different, linear seems to listen to the prompt, original seems to listen more to the base image, channel penalty seems to incorporate a mixture of both


The user must be able to edit the load IPAdapter Model, the Load Image and Apply IPAdapter nodes

if the user does not want to apply IPAdapter then disconnect it and use the default path

if they want to apply multiple IPAdapters then they can to each model checkpoint available

Samplers needs to be fully edited by the user, after this sampler the user will have the ability to connect either an advanced or basic sampler which they would need connect the end of this to either KSampler Adv or Basic Sampler
